org.gvsig.fmap.dal.feature.impl

Class DefaultFeatureReferenceSelection

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gvsig.tools.dispose.impl.AbstractDisposable
      • org.gvsig.fmap.dal.feature.impl.DefaultFeatureReferenceSelection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataSelection, DataSet, FeatureReferenceSelection, Disposable, ComplexObservable, Observable, Observer, WeakReferencingObservable, Persistent, Visitable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultFeatureSelection

    public class DefaultFeatureReferenceSelection
extends AbstractDisposable
implements FeatureReferenceSelection
    Default implementation of a FeatureReferenceSelection, based on the usage of a java.util.Set to store individual selected or not selected FeatureReferences, depending on the usage of the reverse() method.

      • update

        public void update(Observable observable,
          Object notification)
        Description copied from interface: Observer
        Called whenever a Observable object is changed and this Observer has registered on it to receive notifications.

        Implementations of this method will be called for each simple notification or, if a complex notification is created, for each of the child notifications.

        In the latter case, don't assume any ordering in the notification between this Observer and other Observers listening to the same Observable.

        In a complex notification scenario, if you want to receive only the complex notification and not each of the child notifications, just implement the ComplexObserver and prepare this method implementation to handle receiving DefaultComplexNotification instances as well as direct notification objects.

        Specified by:
        update in interface Observer
        Parameters:
        observable - the observable object.
        notification - the notification data.

      • endComplexNotification

        public void endComplexNotification()
        Description copied from interface: ComplexObservable
        Ends the complex notification mode. All notifications stored while in complex notification mode, will be notified to the registered Observers.

        If a observer is a ComplexObserver, it will be notified with a single DefaultComplexNotification instead of each of the notifications.

        Some important notes to take into account when calling this method.

        • Observers must not rely in the order used to perform the notifications. The notifications order is maintained, but the notification to all the observers might be performed for each notification to all observers, or for each observer all notifications.
        • The notification process works as an atomic action, so if while an Observer is processing a notification another Observer is registered to the source Observable, it won't get any of the notifications currently being notified, but future ones.

        Specified by:
        endComplexNotification in interface ComplexObservable
